<TD>
<FONT CLASS="ArticleSource"><BIG>Aradune:</BIG></FONT> 
<FONT CLASS="ArticleHead"><BIG>What's the 411?</BIG></FONT>
<FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </FONT><FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthor">Csenicier</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=RIGHT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleTime>07/23/2001 11:15 AM CDT</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=LEFT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleText>
Here's the skinny on the latest <b>Ask Brad</b>.<p>Last week Verant tipped their hand on some of the upcoming Shadows of Luclin spells.  Brad confirms the rumors that Wizards will receive pet spells, or <b>familiars</b>.  He makes the comment that they will be &quot;more persistent&quot; than traditional pets.  Perhaps they will survive the trip across a zone border?<p>Similar to the recently added zone <b>The Warrens</b>, all the zones in SoL will employ the same trivial loot code.  This is bad news for high level item farmers.  Good news for everyone else.<p>Do you want to group in Sebilis or Velketors?  When you're not raiding, high level players have limited options for experience grouping.  Luclin will try to address this as it will be less raid oriented and more focused on &quot;regular content&quot; from levels 1 to 60.  Brad does go on to say that there will be &quot;some nasty, tough, raid content as well&quot;.<p>We've heard this before but it's worth repeating.  Luclin will, of course, include all new character models.  The plan still is to allow you to select a new face for your existing character so that you can choose the new model that suits you best.<p>Oh, and to those who fear that the world of Norrath is flat, &quot;seek the dragon statue, and then the globe&quot;.<p>Well, that's it.  There's more in the full article in the developers corner but nothing else of real interest.
</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
